=Bio=

'''1.'''

"Independent researcher, I'm passionate about open cooperative (P2P) networks, co-creativity, systems thinking, collective intelligence, alternative currencies, commons, patterns, design, permaculture, ...

I focus my research on three topics related topics:

- Open social innovation as an intellectual framework to facilitate the transfer of practices accross various communities in the spirit of free/open source software: http://www.lilianricaud.com/web-strategy/open-research/open-social-innovation-open-sourcing-social-innovation-to-promote-sharing-sustainable-social-practices/

- Documenting co-creative events formats and patterns as a way to increase the quantity and the quality of our 'Do-it-together' vocabulary: http://www.lilianricaud.com/web-strategy/open-research/co-creative-event-pattern-language/

- Stigmergy as new model of collaboration in large groups: http://www.lilianricaud.com/travail-en-reseau/principes-cles-pour-mettre-en-oeuvre-une-cooperation-stigmergique/



'''2.'''

"I’m a freelance web consultant and teacher, with expertise in online collaborative work and enterprise 2.0, social Media & interactive marketing, ergonomy, utilisability, webdesign.

Originally trained as a plant biologist before switching to web consulting, I worked in top research labs (INRA, CEA, University of Cambridge) and my work has been published in several scientific journals (Nature, PLoS, …).
Since 2005, I research and study the new online tools and practices in social media, collaborative work, open innovation, keeping daily watch on the latest trends.

I’m currently a freelance web consultant advising companies in planning, designing and implementing efficient communication strategies for promotion or collaborative work.

I’m also a digital nomad, a music lover and nature lover."
(http://www.lilianricaud.com/web-strategy/about/)

